A vast flock of luminous origami cranes in gradient colors from deep indigo to warm gold, soaring upward from a single pair of cupped hands at the bottom of the frame, the paper birds multiplying and transforming as they rise higher into a twilight sky, some cranes dissolving into smaller cranes that scatter in different directions, creating an endless cascade of multiplication and movement, the hands below remaining full despite the continuous release, rendered in a Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures, delicate linework, and that signature warm ethereal glow filtering through the paper wings, creating dappled light patterns across the scene.
